summary: Frontend testing for Token Wellness navigation and back buttons. Tested role-select, athlete-token, athlete-wellness, and generate-wellness-token pages. Back buttons work correctly on athlete-token and athlete-wellness pages. Minor visual issue found on generate-wellness-token page where back button exists functionally but icon is not rendered.

ui_bugs.issue: Back button exists and functions correctly (router.back() triggered) but the arrow-back icon is not visually rendered on web

action_items: OPTIONAL: Investigate why Ionicons arrow-back is not rendering in generate-wellness-token header while it renders correctly in athlete-token and athlete-wellness pages
critical_code_review_comments: athlete-token.tsx has testID='back-button' while generate-wellness-token.tsx lacks testID on the back button - should add for consistency
Back buttons use router.replace() in athlete pages but router.back() in generate-wellness-token - design choice is appropriate for each use case
All data-testid attributes are properly set on key interactive elements (coach-button, athlete-button, token-input, validate-button, submit-button)
seed_data_creation: Used existing test data from previous iterations
context_for_next_testing_agent: Navigation flow tested: role-select -> athlete-token (back works) -> athlete-wellness (back works). Generate-wellness-token back button works functionally but icon not visible. Login page does not have back button (uses router.replace). Token 9UDZAX was used for testing and may need refresh if expired.
